ACKNOWLEDGMENT OF DEPENDENCIES

This Backend Software uses the following open-source projects and frameworks,
each with its own separate license:

**Commerce Engine:**
  • MedusaJS (https://github.com/medusajs/medusa) — MIT License
    E-commerce platform framework and API foundation

**Runtime & Language:**
  • Node.js (https://github.com/nodejs/node) — MIT License
    JavaScript runtime environment

  • TypeScript (https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript) — Apache 2.0 License
    Typed superset of JavaScript

**Database & ORM:**
  • PostgreSQL (https://www.postgresql.org) — PostgreSQL License
    Open-source relational database

  • TypeORM (https://github.com/typeorm/typeorm) — MIT License
    ORM for TypeScript and JavaScript

**API & Web Framework:**
  • Express.js (https://github.com/expressjs/express) — MIT License
    Web application framework (if used)

  • NestJS (https://github.com/nestjs/nest) — MIT License
    Progressive Node.js framework (if used)

**Payment Processing:**
  • Stripe SDK / Razorpay SDK — Respective proprietary licenses
    Payment gateway integrations

**Authentication & Security:**
  • Passport.js (https://github.com/jaredhanson/passport) — MIT License
    Authentication middleware (if used)

  • JWT (JSON Web Tokens) — Open standard
    Secure token-based authentication

**File Storage:**
  • DigitalOcean Spaces SDK — MIT License
    Cloud object storage integration

  • AWS SDK / Cloud SDKs — Various open-source licenses
    Cloud service integrations

**Logging & Monitoring:**
  • Winston / Pino — MIT License
    Logging libraries

  • Sentry (https://sentry.io) — Proprietary with open-source components
    Error tracking and performance monitoring

**Other Dependencies:**
  All other npm packages and their dependencies listed in package.json
  and yarn.lock (or package-lock.json)

This Software acknowledges these and other open-source projects that make
this backend possible. You MUST comply with all dependency licenses
independently in addition to this License.

For a complete list of dependencies, versions, and their licenses, see:
  • package.json — Direct dependencies
  • yarn.lock or package-lock.json — All resolved dependencies
  • npm ls --depth=0 — List installed packages

